# Lin Language TODO
# Format: [ ] pending  [/] in progress  [x] done
# Tiers: 🔴 blocking  🟡 important  🟢 nice-to-have

# Architecture reference (PIC spec):
#   pic.graph  → abstract combinator graph (γ⁺ γ⁻ δ ε ω + boundaries)
#   pic.reduce → scheduling-aware reduction ops (annihilate/dup/erase/fire_op)
#   pic.runtime→ CPU/GPU dispatch (cpu_dispatch, gpu_batch, sync_point)
#
# Node set (5 nodes):
#   γ⁺  Constructor  principal(+), aux(left, right)
#   γ⁻  Destructor   principal(-), aux(left, right)
#   δ   Duplicator   principal(*), aux(left, right)
#   ε   Eraser       principal(*), no aux
#   ω   Operation    principal(+/-), aux(inputs..., outputs...)
#
# 4 Rules: Annihilation, Duplication, Erasure, Congruence
# Rules should be mostly user-defined via a lookup table.
# Goal: CPU, GPU, and high-perf GPU shaders — unified pipeline via MLIR.

## 🔴 Tier 0 — Architecture (foundational correctness)

[x] A1. pic.reduce pass: implement reduction rules in target-independent MLIR
        - PicReduceToRuntimePass walks pic.graph functions
        - Emits pic_reduce.annihilate/duplicate/erase/fire_op ops
        - Handles boundary merge (B2)

[x] A2. Rule lookup table (user-extensible dispatch)
        - APPROVED: table keyed on (agentType_A, label_A, agentType_B, label_B)
        - Runtime struct pic.reduction_rule with fields: typeA, labelA, typeB, labelB, handler
        - Default rules: annihilate, duplicate, erase, fire_op, merge_boundary
        - register_rule() runtime function for std library to add custom rules
        - Replace if-else CondBrOp chain with table lookup loop
        - Same table, different lowering for CPU (LLVM) vs GPU (SPIR-V)

[x] A3. Fix γ⁺/γ⁻ encoding for function agents
        - A3 FIX: γ⁺/γ⁻ are both NODE_CON=1 per PIC spec
        - Polarity is in port value, not node type
        - Collapsed checkBeta block - function app is now standard annihilation
        - Collapsed isEither block - ω(branch)⋈num covered by rules
        - Simplified dispatch to just annihilation vs commutation
        - Now uses rule lookup table from A2

[x] A4. Boundary [ ] lowering
        - BoundaryOp now lowered in PicReduceToRuntimePass
        - getNextBoundaryId() for unique boundary tracking
        - B1: containment - effect bubbling via wire polarity
        - B2: merge_boundary op when boundaries meet
        - B3: collapse deferred to runtime E-graph hashing

## 🔴 Tier 1 — High-Level Syntax & Semantics (Wellspring Alignment)

[x] 1. AST_PAIR lowering in lowerExpression
        - Emit a pair agent that holds two ports ✅
        - Wire left/right sub-expressions into p1/p2 ✅
        - Field access (.0 / .1) added to AST with TOKEN_DOT lexer support ✅
        - parseFieldAccess() added, handles chained field access ✅
        - parseGroupingExpr() updated to handle postfix field access after any expression ✅
        - Unblocks: std library result.0/result.1 pattern, multiple return values

[x] 2. `either` reduction rule (if/else at runtime)
        - CPU worker_thread: BRANCH ~ NUM fires, selects true/false, erases loser
        - NODE_BRANCH=7 added to encoding (to be folded into ω via A3)
        - TODO(A1): GPU kernel parity via unified pic.reduce pass

[x] 3. Beta-reduction (function application at runtime)
        - Phase 1: γ(+,f) ~ γ(-,f) wires aux ports (p1↔p1, p2↔p2)
        - Collapsed checkBeta into standard annihilation per A3
        - GPU kernel parity via unified pic.reduce pass (A1)
        - Phase 2: body-graph cloning for multi-arg / closures

[x] 4. mlir-op full pipeline connection
        - PARSE:    AST_MLIR_OP captured correctly (name + interface + payload) ✅
        - LOWER:    lowerExpression emits RegistryOp(name, payload) + ω agent ✅
        - REGISTRY: RegistryOp collection exists in LoweringPasses.cpp (STR_ only) ⚠️
                    Fix: extend to collect non-STR_ entries from mlir-op declarations
        - DISPATCH: switch-case payload cloning machinery exists and works ✅
                    (used by std lib ops; user ops just need to reach it)
        - RUNTIME:  ω(+, f) ⋈ ω(-, f) → fires cloned MLIR payload for label f
        - Connects to A2: user-defined mlir-op rules register to the lookup table

[x] 5. Full Syntax Migration (word-call REMOVED for pure Rebol style)
        - REMOVED: word-call parsing (no longer supports paren-less calls)
        - Now requires parentheses: (print "hello") or (fib n - 1)
        - Done in commit e342159

[x] 6. Path Access Support (`/` notation)
        - Parser: Recognize `identifier/index` and `identifier/field`
        - Lowering: Map `/N` (1-indexed) to `proj_N` agents in PIC graph
        - Support nested paths: `engine/world/bodies/1`
        - ✅ Works with arrays and blocks

[x] 7. Data Blocks vs. Code Blocks
        - Parser: Distinguish between block as statement-list vs. block as data-literal
        - Lowering: For data blocks, emit a linked structure of Pair agents in the graph
        - Unblocks: `copy [pos vel force]` pattern in Wellspring

[x] 8. Module Headers & Metadata
        - Parser: Recognize `Name: module [ metadata ]` syntax
        - Storage: Capture module name and property block
        - ✅ DONE: Name: module [ version: "1.0" ] parses correctly

[x] 9. Refined Assignment (Multi-assignment)
        - Multi-line style: x: 1 \n y: 2 \n z: 3 works
        - Single-line (a: 1 b: 2) would require lexer position save/restore
        - ✅ Partially done: separate lines work

[x] 10. Full Syntax Migration (Unified Rebol Style)
        - REMOVED word-call syntax (requires parentheses)
        - REMOVED implicit return (requires explicit return: [Type!])
        - PRESERVED void return via return: []
        - examples/*.lin use new full syntax
        - test/ suite updated to use parentheses
        - std/*.lin library files use clean syntax

## 🟡 Tier 2 — Language Completeness

[ ] 11. Closure / captured variable support
        - Thread outer-scope bindings into inner γ⁺ function agents via aux ports
        - Multi-use bindings → δ (duplicator) nodes for sharing

[x] 12. Binary operators via std library
        - All 12 operators (+, -, *, /, <, >, <=, >=, ==, !=, &&, ||) work
        - Parsed in Parser.c and emitted as Call(op_name) AST nodes
        - Users import "std/math.lin" to use binary operations
        - No built-in operators — all defined in std/

[ ] 13. Type checking / type-directed dispatch
        - AstFuncArg.type_name is parsed but never used — wire it up
        - Lightweight structural type check with source locations on mismatch
        - Drives ω label selection (e.g., llvm.add vs. llvm.fadd)

[ ] 14. Multiple return values via pairs
        - Depends on item 1 (AST_PAIR lowering)
        - Function return types as pairs; .0/.1 access compiles correctly

## 🟢 Tier 3 — Developer Experience

[x] 15. `linc run` command
        - Compile to binary and execute in one step: linc run file.lin -o /tmp/bin
        - Prints exit code and stdout; requires pre-built binary path

[ ] 16. @gpu / @cpu per-function annotations
        - Parser: recognize @identifier before func/mlir-op declarations
        - Lowering: attach dispatch attr to γ⁺ / ω agents
        - pic.reduce → pic.runtime routing via annotation (no user pragma needed)
        - Goal: graph structure encodes parallelism; annotations only override

[ ] 17. Human-readable error messages
        - Source location (file:line:col) on all parse and lowering errors
        - Type mismatch messages instead of raw MLIR verifier output

[ ] 18. Node GC / arena reset
        - Erasure propagation IS GC (Rule 3: parallel ε sweep)
        - Arena reset after reduction for long-running programs
        - GPU GC: thousands of ε nodes propagate simultaneously via gpu.launch

## 🔵 Architecture — Long-Term

[ ] 19. Unified CPU/GPU reduction pipeline via pic.reduce
        - Define link/annihilate/dup/erase/fire_op in scf+arith+memref dialect
        - Lower once to LLVM for CPU; once to gpu+spirv for GPU
        - Target: CPU (std LLVM), general GPU (Vulkan/SPIR-V), shader GPU (perf)

[ ] 20. 128-bit node layout audit
        - Current: int32_t[4] per node — correct size per spec ✅
        - Verify: polarity encoded in port value (atomic bit-field), not separate field
        - Lock-free redex detection via single atomic CAS on principal port

[ ] 21. E-graph congruence (Rule 4)
        - Inside boundaries: hash normal forms, merge identical subgraphs
        - Fires continuously during reduction (not a post-pass)
        - GPU: congruence hashing as a parallel reduce kernel
        - Requires boundary lowering (A4)

[ ] 22. Hot code reloading
        - Recompile a function's interaction net graph at runtime
        - Swap γ⁺ agent's aux wire to new body graph atomically
        - Requires stable node indexing and generational GC (item 12)

[ ] 23. Approximate / stochastic accuracy system
        - add-noise/accuracy 0.95 [img kernel] syntax
        - Carry accuracy metadata through ω agent attributes
        - Lower to LLVM approx passes (PUMPKIN-style) for hardware hints
        - Part of std, not a language primitive

